1. (a) Identify the type of Operating System suitable for this environment and justify your answer. (4 Marks)
Answer:
The suitable operating system is a Multi-user Time-Sharing Operating System.
Justification:
1. It allows multiple users to access the same computer simultaneously.
2. CPU time is shared among users using time slicing.
3. Each user feels they have a dedicated system.
Examples: Linux, UNIX.

(b) State any two responsibilities of the kernel in managing multiple user processes. (2 Marks)
Process Scheduling – Allocates CPU time among processes.
Memory Management – Allocates and deallocates memory for each process.

(C) PROGRAM:
#include <stdio.h>
#include <unistd.h>

int main()
{
    pid_t pid;

    pid = fork();

    if(pid == 0)
    {
        printf("Child Process\n");
        printf("Child PID = %d\n", getpid());
        printf("Parent PID = %d\n", getppid());
    }
    else
    {
        printf("Parent Process\n");
        printf("Parent PID = %d\n", getpid());
    }

    return 0;
}

